--- Description ---
Patch matron input to read virtual encoder/key events from FIFO instead of GPIO.

Target file: matron/src/hardware/input.c (or the encoder/key specific files)

Environment variable: NORNS_INPUT_FIFO (path to FIFO, e.g. /tmp/norns-input-1)

Protocol: 4-byte frames [type:1][id:1][value_lo:1][value_hi:1]
  - type 0 = encoder delta (id 0-2 = E1-E3, value = signed int16 delta)
  - type 1 = key state (id 0-2 = K1-K3, value 0=up 1=down)

Changes:

1. In input init:
   const char *fifo = getenv("NORNS_INPUT_FIFO");
   if (fifo) {
       input_fifo_fd = open(fifo, O_RDONLY | O_NONBLOCK);
       /* Start FIFO poll thread instead of GPIO thread */
   }

2. FIFO poll thread (replaces GPIO polling):
   while (running) {
       uint8_t frame[4];
       ssize_t n = read(input_fifo_fd, frame, 4);
       if (n == 4) {
           uint8_t type = frame[0];
           uint8_t id = frame[1];
           int16_t value = (int16_t)(frame[2] | (frame[3] << 8));
           if (type == 0 && id < 3) {
               /* Post encoder event: event_post(EVENT_ENC, id, value) */
           } else if (type == 1 && id < 3) {
               /* Post key event: event_post(EVENT_KEY, id, value) */
           }
       }
       usleep(1000);  /* 1ms poll interval */
   }

3. Skip all GPIO/libgpiod/libevdev initialization when NORNS_INPUT_FIFO is set.

4. Coexists with Maiden REPL (Maiden uses OSC on port 10111, unaffected).
